<P><PB N="61" REF="001321_0067_0FB2872D47AA3820">Four Propositions will Clear the Doctrine.</P>
<DIV3 N="1" TYPE="proposition">
<HEAD>PROPOSITION I.</HEAD>
<P><HI>That sometimes Death comes on men <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ery Suddenly.</HI> It has ever been so in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ll Ages of the world; therefore if <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f it be so in our Dayes, we need not wonder at it: Numb. 6.9. <HI>If a man Dye very Suddenly.</HI> Implying that men <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Dye so. Death does often over|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ake them when they no more think <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f it than the Fishes of the Net, or the Bird of the Snare in which it is taken: Eccl. 9&punc; 12. <HI>Man knows not his time; but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> the Fishes are taken in an Evil Net, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd the Bird in the Snare, so are the Sons <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f men Snared in all Evil time, when it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">alleth Suddenly upon them.</HI> It is true, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hat Death does sometimes give warn|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">g of its approaches, by lingering <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ckness, by bodily Pains, by decayes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">rough Age; but it is not always so: <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">. 21.13&punc; <HI>They go down to the Grave <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Moment.</HI> Ver. 23. <HI>One Dyes in his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> strength, being wholly at Ease.</HI> And <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">etimes when Sickness overtakes <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">, it makes quick work of them: It
