uses to be so when God visits a Peo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ple with the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">gue. As in <HI>Egy<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI>&punc; Psal. 78 50. <HI>God gave their Lives <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> to the Pesti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ence</HI>; and then at mid<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">night they were struck Dead in a Mo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ment. Thus in <HI>Davids</HI> time, 2 Sa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc; 24.15. Tis said, that <HI>from the morning <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> the time a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">nted:</HI> which is supposed to intend the Evening Sacrifice&punc; the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> dyed by the Plague Seventy Tho<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">sand Men, in (as some compute it) <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">bout Twelve Hours time. Sometime<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> yea oftentimes, men are subject <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Death&punc; without any Sickness at <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; Some accident not thought of puts <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> end to their dayes. It may be an <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">expected fall brings sudden Death o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> them. As it was with <HI>Eli,</HI> he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> from his Seat, and that fall killed him&punc; Sometimes a fall from an House e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">